# ADR-075 E4-1 — Playwright E2E artifacts
/test-results/
/playwright-report/
/playwright/.cache/

# ADR-077 V-E — visual baselines are a LINUX-only maintained lane.
# `.github/workflows/update-visual-baselines.yml` (the only baseline generator)
# runs on ubuntu-latest and emits `*-chromium-linux.png` exclusively; ci.yml's
# `web-e2e` job is ubuntu-latest too. Windows is a legacy local-dev lane no
# workflow refreshes.
#
# Playwright auto-WRITES a baseline for any spec that has none, so every local
# Windows run drops ~1.3 MB of `*-chromium-win32.png` into the snapshot dirs and
# they surface as untracked files begging to be committed. Committing them would
# bake unreviewed, CI-unverified, in-flight UI in as "expected" — exactly what
# `web/e2e/visual/README.md`'s PR checklist forbids (2026-07-14 사용자 결재:
# visual = out of scope; refresh only via the documented Linux lane).
#
# Ignore them so local runs stop producing commit-able detritus. The 4 win32
# baselines already tracked from `155e127` are unaffected (gitignore does not
# untrack), and `--update-snapshots` can still refresh linux baselines.
e2e/visual/**/*-chromium-win32.png
